But what I do know is, you
don't fucking deserve this.

23:52.797 --> 23:55.247
Thank you for the first
meeting in nine months.

23:56.770 --> 23:59.168
- I thought Gordon was
going to be nice to me.

24:06.023 --> 24:06.967
- That was extraordinary,

24:06.967 --> 24:09.824
the only person who actually
cared about this place,

24:09.824 --> 24:12.827
Mandy, the general manager, has gone.

24:12.827 --> 24:15.646
Those daughters are absolutely screwed.

24:18.249 --> 24:21.117
(birds tweeting)

24:22.274 --> 24:23.369
- [Gordon] I had a dreadful sleep,

24:23.369 --> 24:25.538
I need to get some exercise,
to burn off some of the tension

24:25.538 --> 24:28.194
from all that screaming last night.

24:28.194 --> 24:29.114
- Hi, good morning, darling.

24:29.114 --> 24:30.051
- Hi, how are you?

24:30.051 --> 24:30.950
- I'm well thanks, how are you?

24:30.950 --> 24:32.104
- I'm good.

24:32.104 --> 24:34.138
- God, it was a rough night, that one.

24:34.138 --> 24:37.695
I want to go to the gym and
do some workout and swim.

24:37.695 --> 24:38.563
- Okay.

24:38.563 --> 24:40.052
- What floor is it on?

24:40.052 --> 24:42.263
- It's not, we don't
have one in the building.

24:42.263 --> 24:43.775
There's one right over there.

24:45.276 --> 24:46.145
Yeah.

24:47.882 --> 24:49.082
- Over where?

24:49.082 --> 24:51.741
- Right over here, like down this street,

24:51.741 --> 24:53.191
it's like a rec centre.

24:53.191 --> 24:54.883
- So I have to go out of the hotel?

24:59.781 --> 25:01.167
Fuck this, no chance!

25:01.167 --> 25:03.809
This is all ridiculous, sod that.

25:03.809 --> 25:06.548
A hotel this size, with no gym on site,

25:06.548 --> 25:08.602
is just another example of Vanda and Rina

25:08.602 --> 25:10.896
forgetting who's most
important around here.

25:12.189 --> 25:13.711
- Hey, Gordon.
- Good morning.

25:13.711 --> 25:14.869
Let's have a little catch up.

25:14.869 --> 25:18.197
Hopefully today, I can
finally get through to them.

25:18.197 --> 25:19.065
Good morning.

25:22.877 --> 25:25.942
These are some of your guests.

25:25.942 --> 25:29.435
All I'd like to hear, is just
nothing but the plain truth.

25:29.435 --> 25:33.825
And give these owners an insight
to what you're paying for.

25:33.825 --> 25:35.308
Sir, let's start with you.

25:35.308 --> 25:39.310
- I'll tell you the room
was very disappointing.

25:39.310 --> 25:41.979
We look for historic
buildings when we go places,

25:41.979 --> 25:43.189
and this was just a shame.

25:43.189 --> 25:44.575
It was like it was neglected.

25:44.575 --> 25:46.150
- It was run down down to the ground,

25:46.150 --> 25:47.592
before we purchased this place.

25:47.592 --> 25:49.052
- [Vanda] For about 10 years.
- [Rina] For 10 years.

25:49.052 --> 25:51.488
- You've got to stop blaming people.

25:51.488 --> 25:52.357
Madam, please,

25:52.357 --> 25:53.866
can you give us an insight
to your experience.

25:53.866 --> 25:56.431
- Well, when we came in, we
actually came in the back way.

25:56.431 --> 25:57.849
This dark hallway, where there's...

25:57.849 --> 25:58.994
- It's like a dungeon.

25:58.994 --> 25:59.882
- Yeah, a dungeon.

25:59.882 --> 26:00.751
- Yeah, I entered that way.

26:00.751 --> 26:03.448
I mean, it was like coming
through an entrance to a prison.

26:03.448 --> 26:04.317
- Yeah.

26:05.805 --> 26:06.681
- Madam, please.

26:06.681 --> 26:09.444
- I have severe asthma and allergies,

26:09.444 --> 26:11.060
dusting the top of the doorways,

26:11.060 --> 26:14.058
and it's just caked in white dust.

26:14.058 --> 26:15.752
- Oh, my God.

26:15.752 --> 26:17.337
- It went beyond a comfort issue,

26:17.337 --> 26:19.843
this went to a health hazard issue.

26:22.155 --> 26:24.730
I was literally worried
about my fiance's safety.

26:24.730 --> 26:25.971
And the last thing this place needs

26:25.971 --> 26:28.748
is some kind of, you know,
wrongful death liability.

26:29.948 --> 26:30.904
- Oh, gosh.

26:32.655 --> 26:36.388
- Would any of you come back to stay here?

26:36.388 --> 26:37.354
- Absolutely not.

26:38.874 --> 26:40.793
- Not one of you?

26:40.793 --> 26:41.662
Thank you.

26:41.662 --> 26:43.541
- Thank you, guys.

26:43.541 --> 26:46.199
- Take care, thank you, I'm so sorry.

26:46.199 --> 26:48.316
The complaints from
guests are obvious things

26:48.316 --> 26:50.284
that a hotel owner
should be taking care of,

26:50.284 --> 26:53.697
but these girls haven't got
a clue, or a general manager.

26:53.697 --> 26:54.565
Do you honestly think

26:54.565 --> 26:57.753
that you are capable
of running this hotel?

26:57.753 --> 26:59.296
- When I want something bad enough,

26:59.296 --> 27:00.693
and when I have my mind up to it,

27:00.693 --> 27:03.342
I always, I always accomplish.

27:03.342 --> 27:05.448
- At 32 years of age,

27:05.448 --> 27:08.075
tell me one thing that you've
accomplished in your life,

27:08.075 --> 27:08.944
on your own.

27:15.162 --> 27:18.443
- I worked when I was
14 at a fast food place.

27:19.931 --> 27:21.610
- Are you serious?

27:21.610 --> 27:23.560
You want me to get impressed with that?

27:23.560 --> 27:26.354
- No, no, but I'm just saying...

27:26.354 --> 27:30.025
- Vanda, do you honestly think
that you and your big sister

27:30.025 --> 27:32.590
are capable of running this hotel?

27:32.590 --> 27:37.803
- I want to say yes, but
just my head says, no.

27:40.328 --> 27:44.873
(Rina bursting into tears)

27:44.873 --> 27:47.636
- I feel like a knife has
just been run into my heart,

27:47.636 --> 27:49.693
but I can run this place by myself.

27:51.577 --> 27:52.849
- You have to be honest with yourself.

27:52.849 --> 27:53.965
- I think we can make it

27:53.965 --> 27:56.124
with the positive
reinforcement that I use.

27:56.124 --> 27:56.992
- Oh, God!

27:56.992 --> 27:58.272
- I would shit myself,

27:58.272 --> 28:02.557
asking you to run my dog up
the hill, let alone a hotel.

28:02.557 --> 28:05.425
(dramatic music)

28:07.656 --> 28:09.689
- [Narrator] Pipestone,
Minnesota's Calumet Inn,

28:09.689 --> 28:11.378
is in a dreadful state.

28:11.378 --> 28:12.348
The food is awful...

28:12.348 --> 28:15.095
- It is absolutely, fucking disgusting.

28:15.095 --> 28:15.963
- Oh, gross!

28:15.963 --> 28:17.218
- And the rooms are just as bad.

28:17.218 --> 28:19.671
- Oh, that's mouldy.
- Oh, man.

28:20.726 --> 28:22.942
- And the owners are totally useless.

28:22.942 --> 28:24.934
I would shit myself

28:24.934 --> 28:28.993
asking you to run my dog up
the hill, let alone a hotel.

28:32.014 --> 28:33.077
There's only one person

28:33.077 --> 28:35.757
that could help me save this place...

28:35.757 --> 28:38.600
Unless I can convince Mandy to come back

28:38.600 --> 28:40.637
and take on the role as a general manager.

28:40.637 --> 28:45.527
Then quite frankly, Rina
and Vanda are screwed.

28:45.527 --> 28:48.533
And I'll tell them to
close the hotel tonight.

28:52.004 --> 28:55.829
(knocking) Hi, darling,
have you got two minutes?

28:57.271 --> 28:58.834
You had every right to walk out,

28:58.834 --> 28:59.703
how are you feeling?

28:59.703 --> 29:01.505
- Bitter, but I'm okay.

29:01.505 --> 29:03.232
- Life's too short.
- I'll get over it.

29:03.232 --> 29:04.101
- Watching the way you work,

29:04.101 --> 29:05.631
and the way you feel for the place,

29:05.631 --> 29:08.480
and how much energy you
put in to that hotel,

29:09.520 --> 29:13.117
you are a bloody good general manager.

29:13.117 --> 29:15.104
- Thank you.
- You know your job.

29:15.104 --> 29:16.235
- Thank you.

29:16.235 --> 29:19.686
- If you were given the
absolute control of that place,

29:19.686 --> 29:20.555
to run it,

29:23.412 --> 29:24.455
would you come back?

29:26.216 --> 29:28.476
- Hm, that's tough.

29:28.476 --> 29:30.075
I just, I don't like them.

29:31.730 --> 29:32.598
- I know.

29:32.598 --> 29:33.982
- And after everything that's been said,

29:33.982 --> 29:38.080
I don't, I mean, I, I don't know.

29:38.080 --> 29:41.128
I just, I don't know.

29:42.918 --> 29:45.525
- If I was Mandy, I don't
know what I'd do either.

29:46.526 --> 29:49.490
Take care and please, think about it.

29:56.348 --> 29:58.892
I really don't know what's
going to happen at this hotel.

29:58.892 --> 30:01.405
Are Rina and Vanda capable of change?

30:01.405 --> 30:02.427
Do they have it in them,

30:02.427 --> 30:04.909
to shoulder the
responsibility of this hotel?

30:04.909 --> 30:07.154
I need to have a proper
chat with their mum.

30:08.748 --> 30:09.705
(Gordon knocking)

30:09.705 --> 30:12.114
- Yeah?
- Hello?

30:12.114 --> 30:12.982
- Come in.

30:16.086 --> 30:17.004
Hi.

30:17.004 --> 30:20.080
- It smells incredible up there.

30:20.080 --> 30:21.125
- Come on in.

30:21.125 --> 30:21.993
- What are you cooking?

30:21.993 --> 30:23.219
- I am cooking green curry.

30:23.219 --> 30:24.699
- It smells incredible.

30:24.699 --> 30:27.098
And who's whose recipes are these?

30:27.098 --> 30:28.923
- Oh, I just make up.

30:29.834 --> 30:31.744
- Do you mind if I have a little taste?

30:31.744 --> 30:33.179
- Yup, sure.

30:33.179 --> 30:34.717
A little bit spicy, maybe?

30:34.717 --> 30:35.814
- No, that's perfect.

30:35.814 --> 30:37.900
That is absolutely perfect, my God, hmm.

30:39.235 --> 30:40.475
- Wow, that is delicious,

30:40.475 --> 30:43.645
that's the tastiest food I've
eaten, since I've been here.

30:43.645 --> 30:44.792
- Thank you.

30:44.792 --> 30:49.005
- Amazing, you're a very, very good cook.

30:49.005 --> 30:51.215
How many times a week do
you cook for your daughters?

30:51.215 --> 30:53.155
- Seven days a week. (laughing)

30:53.155 --> 30:54.823
- Those babies need to grow up.

30:54.823 --> 30:56.533
- Yeah, I know that.

30:56.533 --> 30:57.982
I spoil them.

30:57.982 --> 31:00.061
- When was the last time you had a break?

31:02.234 --> 31:04.732
- Not really, not at all.

31:07.252 --> 31:09.755
Sometimes I get frustrated, I tell them,

31:09.755 --> 31:12.114
you need to do the work now by yourself.

31:13.435 --> 31:14.947
- [Gordon] Rina and
Vanda treat their mother

31:14.947 --> 31:16.313
as their personal chef,

31:16.313 --> 31:19.233
so she's stuck at the hotel,
working seven days a week.

31:19.233 --> 31:21.037
It's time the girls grew up.

31:21.037 --> 31:24.387
I wanted to talk to all four
of you, to shed some light.

31:25.541 --> 31:28.555
If you want to teach your
daughters responsibility,

31:28.555 --> 31:31.568
like I have to as a father
with three daughters,

31:31.568 --> 31:33.236
I'd buy them a fucking goldfish,

31:34.832 --> 31:35.742
not a hotel.

31:37.595 --> 31:39.055
Jim, do you want to be here?

31:39.993 --> 31:42.676
- I wouldn't want to stay
here on a permanent basis.

31:43.841 --> 31:44.709
- Rita?

31:45.824 --> 31:49.342
- No.
- No.

31:49.342 --> 31:51.949
Vanda, do you want to be here?

31:53.979 --> 31:55.196
- No, I don't.

31:57.544 --> 31:58.413
- Rina?

31:59.374 --> 32:01.611
- I'm not happy here.

32:01.611 --> 32:02.862
I'm not, I'll be honest.

32:03.777 --> 32:04.928
- That's not what I'm asking, my darling.

32:04.928 --> 32:08.358
I'm asking you, do you want to be here?

32:11.035 --> 32:11.903
- No.

32:12.797 --> 32:14.298
- I don't think you do either.

32:14.298 --> 32:15.643
You need to go back to Minneapolis,

32:15.643 --> 32:17.639
you need to get into the city.

32:17.639 --> 32:18.629
That's what you need to do.

32:18.629 --> 32:23.842
- Thank you, that's all I want. (crying)

32:25.480 --> 32:28.087
I want that so bad, thank you.

32:33.200 --> 32:36.223
I'm sorry, this is just something
I've been afraid to say.

32:38.906 --> 32:39.928
- [Gordon] Each one of you

32:39.928 --> 32:43.025
are actually trapped inside this hotel.

32:43.025 --> 32:44.401
- What do we do?

32:44.401 --> 32:48.879
- I would like you to decide as a family.

32:48.879 --> 32:50.022
Do you want a proper general manager

32:50.022 --> 32:51.648
to run the hotel for you,

32:51.648 --> 32:53.966
or do you want to sell
it, or shut it down?

32:54.891 --> 32:56.038
The decision is yours.

32:57.834 --> 33:00.701
(dramatic music)

33:02.673 --> 33:03.541
- [Narrator] Coming up,

33:03.541 --> 33:04.953
the family has come to a decision

33:04.953 --> 33:06.434
about whether to close the doors

33:06.434 --> 33:09.051
of this historic Calumet Inn.

33:09.051 --> 33:10.344
- I'm very sorry...

33:12.706 --> 33:16.355
(electrical interference)

33:18.425 --> 33:19.436
- [Narrator] The owners of Pipestone,

33:19.436 --> 33:21.564
Minnesota's historic Calumet Inn,

33:21.564 --> 33:24.598
have made a decision, about
whether to shut the hotel down,

33:24.598 --> 33:28.226
sell it, or get a proper general
manager to run it for them.

33:28.226 --> 33:31.678
- I have no idea what's
going to happen, I'm nervous.

33:31.678 --> 33:34.827
I'm very sorry for the way that
you guys have been treated.

33:34.827 --> 33:37.924
- And we have made a decision here

33:37.924 --> 33:40.012
that will turn this place around.

33:43.432 --> 33:48.549
And that means us stepping
out of the picture.

33:48.549 --> 33:53.450
- Tomorrow, there is going to
be a new general manager here.

33:53.450 --> 33:54.711
Somebody actually in charge,

33:54.711 --> 33:57.089
someone with the
authority from the owners,

33:57.089 --> 33:59.229
to run this place on their behalf.

34:00.498 --> 34:02.792
Stay there, let me get
them for you, please.

34:05.931 --> 34:07.474
Ladies and gentlemen,

34:07.474 --> 34:11.918
let me introduce you to the
Calumet's new general manager.

34:13.918 --> 34:16.327
Good to see you, say hello to your team.

34:16.327 --> 34:18.485
- After talking with Gordon, I realised,

34:18.485 --> 34:21.165
everybody that works there,
is like my second family.

34:21.165 --> 34:22.958
I care too much about the Calumet,

34:22.958 --> 34:25.335
to allow the doors to be closed.

34:25.335 --> 34:27.514
- I'm pleased you're back.

34:27.514 --> 34:30.163
You are an asset to this hotel.

34:30.163 --> 34:33.614
These two young girls
are leaving this hotel.

34:33.614 --> 34:35.679
- This is exactly what
I've wanted all along.

34:35.679 --> 34:38.806
I've always wanted a true
general manager to run the place,

34:38.806 --> 34:40.184
and I would come here on the weekends,

34:40.184 --> 34:42.123
to help out with the decorations.

34:42.123 --> 34:44.146
- They know that it's not healthy.

34:44.146 --> 34:45.658
They know they can't continue.

34:45.658 --> 34:47.712
- Oh, I'm beyond ready to give Mandy,

34:47.712 --> 34:50.694
you know, full reins and full
control as general manager.

34:50.694 --> 34:52.436
I have full faith in her.

34:52.436 --> 34:56.231
She's a very powerful, very
competent, very strong lady.

34:56.231 --> 34:58.765
- Tomorrow, we are relaunching this hotel

34:58.765 --> 35:00.444
under new management

35:00.444 --> 35:02.216
and there are going to
be a lot of changes.

35:02.216 --> 35:05.574
I want all of you to get out
of here and get some rest,

35:05.574 --> 35:07.169
because tomorrow is one hell of a day.

35:07.169 --> 35:08.038
- Yeah.

35:08.038 --> 35:09.056
- Thank you.

35:09.056 --> 35:10.579
- Today, everyone wins,

35:10.579 --> 35:12.550
as the family is free to leave Pipestone,

35:12.550 --> 35:14.061
the staff get a proper leader,

35:14.061 --> 35:17.169
and Mandy gets the
freedom to be in charge.

35:17.169 --> 35:19.849
And overnight, the interior
of this historic building

35:19.849 --> 35:22.007
has got what it has long deserved too,

35:22.007 --> 35:24.207
a wonderful transformation.

35:24.207 --> 35:25.221
- Good morning.

35:25.221 --> 35:26.230
- Hi.

35:26.230 --> 35:29.713
- Welcome, to the new Calumet Inn.

35:29.713 --> 35:33.435
This is incredibly historic
and a very special hotel,

35:33.435 --> 35:34.304
but now it's somewhere,

35:34.304 --> 35:37.606
where guests are going to be
incredibly well looked after.

35:37.606 --> 35:39.361
Come with me, let's go.

35:44.155 --> 35:45.024
Come on, ladies.

35:45.024 --> 35:47.610
- Oh, my God!

35:47.610 --> 35:49.799
- Holy macaroni!

35:49.799 --> 35:54.352
(girls squealing in delight)

35:54.352 --> 35:55.759
- I take it, you like it?

35:55.759 --> 35:56.628
- I love it!
- Love it!

35:56.628 --> 35:58.252
- Gone is that disgusting wallpaper,

35:58.252 --> 36:01.536
now we have a stunning, bright,

36:01.536 --> 36:03.340
colourful paint of Kelly Green.

36:03.340 --> 36:07.281
A new mattress, new box frame,
new linen, and new cushions,

36:07.281 --> 36:12.109
and a bed to absolutely disappear in.

36:12.109 --> 36:13.485
Notice how bright it is?

36:13.485 --> 36:15.602
Let's try and keep the
bulbs in the fixtures, Jim,

36:15.602 --> 36:17.940
especially in that rear entrance tunnel.

36:17.940 --> 36:20.013
(everyone laughing)

36:20.013 --> 36:22.422
- Gone is that dreadful
rail in the corner,

36:22.422 --> 36:25.477
we replaced that with a
wonderful tall wardrobe,

36:25.477 --> 36:26.679
how nice is that?

36:26.679 --> 36:27.677
- Oh, yeah.

36:27.677 --> 36:30.617
- Beforehand, the jacuzzi looked awkward,

36:30.617 --> 36:32.098
now we framed the bathtub

36:32.098 --> 36:33.902
with these beautiful custom drapes.

36:33.902 --> 36:36.258
So you can highlight the fact
that it's a stunning jacuzzi,

36:36.258 --> 36:38.761
but we've given it his own space.

36:38.761 --> 36:40.982
- I'm blown away, I mean, you know,

36:40.982 --> 36:43.311
guests are actually going to be happy

36:43.311 --> 36:45.257
to spend their honeymoons here,

36:45.257 --> 36:48.479
and we're going to be proud
to actually show this room.

36:48.479 --> 36:51.544
- This one is really special, I mean,

36:51.544 --> 36:53.807
yeah, let's say a new edition.

36:53.807 --> 36:56.873
Please, welcome to my
favourite room, jump in there.

36:56.873 --> 36:57.834
Let's go.

36:57.834 --> 37:02.005
(everyone screaming in delight)

37:04.286 --> 37:05.162
Gone is the bedroom,

37:05.162 --> 37:08.824
you now have a fabulous,
unique fitness centre.

37:08.824 --> 37:10.480
(everyone clapping)

37:10.480 --> 37:12.701
Where guests, like myself,

37:12.701 --> 37:15.277
do not have to walk a hundred metres.

37:15.277 --> 37:17.987
- This room is actually what
everybody needs in here.

37:17.987 --> 37:19.187
When people are stressed out,

37:19.187 --> 37:20.208
when they want to kill each other,

37:20.208 --> 37:23.284
they could just go in
there, and just relax.

37:23.284 --> 37:25.370
- Can we take a seat, please?

37:25.370 --> 37:26.238
I've got something

37:26.238 --> 37:31.223
that is really going to
put this hotel on the map.

37:32.492 --> 37:33.360
The food before,

37:33.360 --> 37:34.879
lacked the heart you would
get from home cooking.

37:34.879 --> 37:38.133
It turns out, the answer
was right under our noses.

37:38.133 --> 37:42.992
Rita, we've adapted your cooking style,

37:42.992 --> 37:44.932
Rita's Thai specials.

37:44.932 --> 37:45.888
- Wow.
- Aw!

37:46.766 --> 37:50.447
- Rita, when I tasted your
food upstairs my darling,

37:50.447 --> 37:52.710
I was blown away.

37:52.710 --> 37:55.546
Now the legacy is going to continue,

37:55.546 --> 37:58.174
a stunning beef satay,

37:58.174 --> 38:00.895
and then a delicious green chicken curry,

38:00.895 --> 38:02.741
and a phenomenal pad Thai.

38:02.741 --> 38:04.787
Thank you ladies, come on, dig in.

38:04.787 --> 38:06.359
Dig in, dig in.

38:06.359 --> 38:07.965
- [Rina] This is real pad Thai.

38:07.965 --> 38:09.248
- Rita, what do you think, my darling?

38:09.248 --> 38:10.117
- Excellent.

38:10.117 --> 38:11.593
- Yeah?
- Yup.

38:11.593 --> 38:16.150
I am very excited to see
my Thai food on the menu.

38:16.150 --> 38:17.994
It tastes very good, yes.

38:17.994 --> 38:20.478
Thank you, thank you so much.

38:20.478 --> 38:23.606
(everyone clapping)

38:25.055 --> 38:26.307
- Okay, are we ready?

38:26.307 --> 38:27.175
- Guys, all good?

38:27.175 --> 38:28.687
- I'm ready.
- Ready to go?

38:28.687 --> 38:29.556
Yeah, brilliant.

38:29.556 --> 38:30.643
- [Narrator] With a rejuvenated energy,

38:30.643 --> 38:31.874
the staff are ready for the first night

38:31.874 --> 38:33.538
of the Calumet's new life.

38:33.538 --> 38:34.407
- I'm well.

38:34.407 --> 38:35.275
- Welcome to the Calumet Inn,

38:35.275 --> 38:37.014
my name's Mandy, general manager.

38:37.014 --> 38:37.883
- How are we doing tonight?

38:37.883 --> 38:39.169
- We're doing very well.

38:39.169 --> 38:40.837
- All right, we have a new menu.

38:43.093 --> 38:44.824
- First ticket, Jen, good luck.

38:44.824 --> 38:45.693
- Thank you.

38:45.693 --> 38:46.561
- [Gordon] You can do this.

38:46.561 --> 38:48.338
- Oh, this is a whole
new level of Thai food.

38:48.338 --> 38:50.445
It's fresh and I'm really
excited about that,

38:50.445 --> 38:51.956
it's something I've always wanted to do.

38:51.956 --> 38:54.240
- And for the first time,
parents Jim and Rita,

38:54.240 --> 38:55.804
are enjoying their investment,

38:55.804 --> 38:57.306
instead of having to work at it.

38:57.306 --> 38:58.414
- Much better, hey, Jim?

38:58.414 --> 38:59.829
- 1,000% better.

38:59.829 --> 39:00.697
Keep up a good work.

39:00.697 --> 39:03.235
- Yeah, I will. (laughing)

39:03.235 --> 39:04.542
- [Gordon] When Mandy agreed to return,

39:04.542 --> 39:06.471
it was on the condition
that Rina and Vanda

39:06.471 --> 39:07.691
would be out of the picture.

39:07.691 --> 39:10.652
Unfortunately, these sisters
can't stop interfering.

39:10.652 --> 39:12.279
- Are we good?

39:12.279 --> 39:13.374
Excellent.

39:13.374 --> 39:14.604
- And were you still working on that,

39:14.604 --> 39:15.699
or would you like me to take?

39:15.699 --> 39:17.482
Okay, all right, enjoy.

39:17.482 --> 39:19.474
- Ooh, how are you doing tonight?

39:19.474 --> 39:20.360
Do you have a wine list?

39:20.360 --> 39:21.635
I can go grab you one.

39:23.133 --> 39:24.458
Oh, my gosh, I had...

39:24.458 --> 39:27.440
They remade our wine list, I had no idea.

39:27.440 --> 39:29.494
- The hotel can't afford
to lose Mandy again.

39:29.494 --> 39:31.767
With so much at stake,
I've got to step in.

39:31.767 --> 39:33.978
What are you doing?

39:33.978 --> 39:36.848
- I am meeting and greeting the guests.

39:36.848 --> 39:37.815
- What are you doing?

39:37.815 --> 39:39.097
- Hi, I'm helping out.

39:39.097 --> 39:40.182
- Helping out?

39:40.182 --> 39:41.214
Let me just tell you something.

39:41.214 --> 39:42.225
You swanning around,

39:42.225 --> 39:44.363
looking like you're
here to take the cream,

39:44.363 --> 39:46.104
because you want to
meet-and-greet the guests.

39:46.104 --> 39:48.802
You've actually done fuck all tonight.

39:48.802 --> 39:50.317
- What am I supposed to do?

39:50.317 --> 39:52.395
- Get back upstairs and pack, now!

39:54.101 --> 39:58.257
(electrical interference)

39:58.257 --> 40:00.105
- [Gordon] The Calumet's
relaunch is going well.

40:00.105 --> 40:01.912
And the team are handling more guests

40:01.912 --> 40:03.518
than the hotel has seen in years.

40:03.518 --> 40:05.645
- Two rib eyes and a spare rib, I got it.

40:05.645 --> 40:08.304
- [Gordon] The guests are
loving the new rooms upstairs.

40:08.304 --> 40:09.325
- Definitely like the colour,

40:09.325 --> 40:11.724
the green really makes it bright.

40:11.724 --> 40:14.268
- It's a nice mix of old and new.

40:14.268 --> 40:15.137
- Yeah.

40:15.137 --> 40:16.332
- Hey, yeah, I would come back here.

40:16.332 --> 40:17.201
- [Gordon] And I'm really pleased

40:17.201 --> 40:19.982
to see Mandy stepping up and
taking control of the team,

40:19.982 --> 40:20.851
as the general manager.

40:20.851 --> 40:22.443
- You have to communicate with the kitchen

40:22.443 --> 40:23.642
a little bit better.

40:23.642 --> 40:25.873
- [Gordon] There's just
one last detail to address,

40:25.873 --> 40:28.097
Rina and Vanda need to hit the road.

40:29.950 --> 40:30.819
- Hello?

40:30.819 --> 40:33.308
- Vanda, are you finished packing yet?

40:33.308 --> 40:34.768
The taxi is on its way.

40:34.768 --> 40:35.636
- I'm going!

40:37.437 --> 40:40.044
- Okay, ladies, taxi is here.

40:40.044 --> 40:43.094
Hey, listen, safe travels
and good luck, okay?

40:43.094 --> 40:43.962
- Thank you.

40:43.962 --> 40:44.831
- A little present for you,

40:44.831 --> 40:47.751
to teach you responsibility
back in Minneapolis.

40:47.751 --> 40:49.762
(girls squealing)

40:49.762 --> 40:50.630
Please.

40:50.630 --> 40:52.546
- Oh, dear Lord.
- Oh, thank you.

40:52.546 --> 40:54.256
- Now, look after them.

40:54.256 --> 40:56.164
Once you've got the hang
of looking after those,

40:56.164 --> 40:57.269
then we can step up to a cat.

40:57.269 --> 40:58.138
- Okay.

40:58.138 --> 40:59.956
- Once the cat's fine,
then we go up to a dog.

40:59.956 --> 41:00.825
- It'll be fine.

41:00.825 --> 41:02.754
- Look after those fish, good night.

41:02.754 --> 41:05.235
- I'm going to go off
and pursue my dreams.

41:05.235 --> 41:10.448
I'm going to travel and
continue onwards into my 30s

41:11.565 --> 41:14.488
a happy person, not miserable.

41:15.746 --> 41:17.362
- The goldfish!

41:17.362 --> 41:19.288
Don't drop it.

41:19.288 --> 41:21.766
- I will not drop the gold fish.

41:23.410 --> 41:25.746
- I'm going back to Minneapolis
but I'm really excited

41:25.746 --> 41:28.144
to feel free to let out my creativity

41:28.144 --> 41:30.667
and show the world what I'm capable of.

41:30.667 --> 41:32.377
Look, one is bigger, and one is smaller,

41:32.377 --> 41:35.297
the bigger one can be Rina,
the little one can be Vanda.

41:36.944 --> 41:37.813
- What a week!

41:37.813 --> 41:40.557
When I first arrived, they
were two spoiled brats,

41:40.557 --> 41:43.837
that were playing at running a hotel.

41:43.837 --> 41:45.609
The change has been extraordinary.

41:45.609 --> 41:49.791
The key to the turnaround
was in Mandy coming back,

41:49.791 --> 41:54.121
and standing strong as a
proper general manager.

41:57.381 --> 41:59.707
This time it's a proper goodbye,

41:59.707 --> 42:03.349
and I cannot wait to
come back and see you.

42:03.349 --> 42:05.379
- Awesome.
- I believe in you.

42:05.379 --> 42:08.486
You already have made a big
difference, good luck with it.

42:08.486 --> 42:09.887
- Thanks.
- Thank you.

42:09.887 --> 42:11.513
- Well done.
- Thank you so much.

42:11.513 --> 42:12.650
- Good night, darling.

42:12.650 --> 42:14.294
- I feel like a whole new person.

42:14.294 --> 42:16.745
I am ready to just go full bore with this.

42:16.745 --> 42:18.736
Thank you so much, Gordon,

42:18.736 --> 42:21.440
for giving me my job back,
and for believing in me.

42:23.856 --> 42:26.170
- I do hope those goldfish survive,

42:26.170 --> 42:31.383
it's 50/50. (chuckling)

42:59.506 --> 43:00.538
- [Female] One potato, two potato.

43:00.538 --> 43:02.992
- [Rina] I thought Gordon
was going to be nice to me.
